reviews.review_text:
Twenty Years Ago Today! Thanx m.  A decent audience recording considering the arena's acoustics.  Give it a listen.
I am from FL and flew back from CA to hang with friends and see these shows.  I first got on archive in March and this show was not well represented.  I have got my music list in order and have been running through getting shows I was at but couldn't find.  I was greatly amused to notice I was downloading this on it's 20th anniv.  
I was a dumb ass and left my friend's and my tix on the Miami side of the state.  We only noticed this upon arrival at the venue.  UGH!  My friend got both nights pretty quick, but I could only score the second night.  Having come all the way from CA I had to get in.  I decided to try the old trick of using tix with different date.  I somehow made myself invisible without anyone asking me for my tix.  Both nights, problem solved.  However no seat at a reserved show.
Music is always a nice opener but never pounds.  Sugaree has some nice vocal moments from Jerry.  Blow Away is probably the highlight of the set.
Set II has a wonderful opening song combo, the only downside is Playing never really goes anywhere.  Drums/Space is lots of fun.  Energetic 2nd half of this set with a beautiful Stella.  Peace

One of the best shows ever!! My boyfriend (now husband)and I had gone to Florida to stay with his parents while I started art school in Ft. Lauderdale.  Though we had seen the Oxford Plains shows, we hadn't originally planned on the Miami/St. Pete shows.  We were on Florida's upper east coast, and when the tickets went on sale, we bought them at a newly opened ticket agency.  In the half-hour or so it took for all three shows to sell out, only three of us were there to buy Dead tickets!!  What's even more improbable was, shortly before this nights show, we ran into that other guy who bought tickets with us that day!!!  What were the odds?!?!? 
Anyway, these two nights in St. Pete hold some of the best memories for me!  I stood on my seat when Jerry sung 'Sugaree' and imagined he was singing it for me, and 'Smokestack Lightning' totally kicked ass!  I remember crying when I had to go back to school because I was willing to follow them anywhere!  I wound up dropping out of art school and moving back north, and even catching a few more shows, but nothing like the experience of St. Pete!  The atmosphere, the people, the scene. . . unforgettable!
Truckin' - Smokestack Transition That transition from Truckin' to Smokestack makes me think about CSNY's Carry On.
